{
  "stem": "24462.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we came to school.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we were asked questions in mathematics, in geography, everything-- 11 subjects.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And later on, we were waiting outside.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then came the [? shamash, ?] as I mentioned before, [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH], And he called, both of you.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Now, this sign, both of you, meant that we passed.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So usually, they called only the one who passed.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And later on, we got the certificates, and which I have still with me.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the anti-Semit-- anti-Semitism was growing and growing.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We have the feeling that it's getting worse and worse from the newspaper, from the Polish newspapers, and from the, and from the signs put on, in the street-- 'Kalisz without Jews,' or 'Don't buy at Jewish shops,' and so on, and so on.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was growing all the time, all the time.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And from time to time, some-- one of us was beaten.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "One of our student was beaten by the Polish [? sacks. ?] And the situation wasn't very pleasant.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the papers were-- the whole, the politics of the Polish government was slowly, after the death of the Marshal Pilsudski, was changing, and changing against the Jews.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In the Senate and the Sejm, which is the Parliament, were voices against the Jews, against the ritual, ritual slaughter of for kosher beef, and some other things.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And all the time was something against the Jews.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So, the relationship, you know, wasn't good and wasn't pleasant.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And you had the feeling you are not wanted.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And you don't, don't know where to go.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the poster was-- which I remember so well-- was 'Kalisz without the Jews.' This is the one big one was always there.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was-- I remember white and red.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I think white was-- red letters on a white background.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
